 Chief Sanjay Jain  Pravasi Bharatiya Divas ceremony is being hosted yearly in India by the Indian government to celebrate Indians resident in other countries outside India. According to Jain, who was bestowed with the Asiwaju chieftaincy title by Mushin kingdom, non-resident Indians can enjoy the endless possibilities that come with thriving in their state of residence as well as their home state. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .